turns.bot: SCANeR Studio is a comprehensive driving simulation software package developed by AVSimulation, used for vehicle ergonomics and advanced engineering studies, road traffic research and development, human factor studies, and driver training (1.1). It's an open software platform that allows customers to develop their own models and connect personal software or hardware within its general framework (1.1.1). The software is modular and can run on various testing environments, from compact driving simulators like SimEASY to larger ones like SimREAL and SimELITE (1.1.2). SCANeR Studio has an ergonomic interface used for building either a light or heavy vehicle simulation, based on a finely tuned traffic model, offering 4 main modes: Vehicle mode, Terrain mode, Traffic mode, and Analysis mode (1.1.3). For more detailed information, you can refer to the SDK documentation.

You can use various sensors in SCANeR Studio such as Camera, Ultrasonic, Radar, and Lidar sensors (7.19.4.2, 1.3.4.1.7). For more details on how to define these sensors and optimize their performance, please refer to the Safety.cfg file under the "Sensors" tab and the "Options" tab (1.3.4.1.7, 1.3.4.1.8). If you want to process sensors data in a more efficient way, you can create plugins for the LIDAR and SENSORS models using the Sensor Plugin API (7.19.4.1, 7.19.2). For a sample on how to read the outputs of all kinds of Lidar Sensors, please refer to the "LidarPluginSample" folder in the SCANeR™ installation (7.19.4.1.Lidar).

threads.title: What sensors are available in scaner studios

turns.user: What sensors are available in scaner studios
turns.bot: In SCANeR Studios, some examples of available sensors are Traffic, Scenario, Driver, and Sensors (1.3.1.1). For tools that can be considered as sensor-related, there are Controlpad, SensorViewer, MotionView, and Dashboard (1.3.1.1.1). Keep in mind that this list is not exhaustive, and more sensors or tools might exist within the SCANeR architecture. For a comprehensive list of all available sensors and tools, you may want to refer to the official documentation provided by AVSimulation.

threads.title: What sensors can i add to my vehicle

turns.user: What sensors can i add to my vehicle
turns.bot:
In SCANeR Studios, you can add eight types of sensors to your digital vehicle: Camera, EHorizon, GPS, LIDAR, LightSensor, RADAR, Ultrasonic, and Remote OSI (3.9.2). To do this, follow these steps:

1. Navigate to the VEHICLE mode.
2. Under the Sensors item, click on the "•••" button and select "Add sensor configuration."
3. To add sensors to a configuration, click on the "•••" button next to the sensor configuration and select "Add Sensor."

For more details about sensor configurations edition, please refer to the Sensors in the Vehicle Mode Quick Start guide (3.9.3).
